{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NoVuy1yDmcZ17KFmzcXUBc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * AND specification, used to create a new specification that is the AND of two other\n     5→ * specifications.\n     6→ */\n     7→public class AndSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     8→\n     9→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n    10→  private final Specification<T> spec2;\n    11→\n    12→  /**\n    13→   * Create a new AND specification based on two other spec.\n    14→   *\n    15→   * @param spec1 Specification one.\n    16→   * @param spec2 Specification two.\n    17→   */\n    18→  public AndSpecification(Specification<T> spec1, Specification<T> spec2) {\n    19→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    20→    this.spec2 = spec2;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    24→  @Override\n    25→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    26→    return spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t) && spec2.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    27→  }\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"457d7854-aa8d-419e-ab43-8c85809b7113"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016qx3M5oPEfTLApLisfJ67i","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/** NOT decorator, used to create a new specifcation that is the inverse (NOT) of the given spec. */\n     4→public class NotSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     5→\n     6→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n     7→\n     8→  /**\n     9→   * Create a new NOT specification based on another spec.\n    10→   *\n    11→   * @param spec1 Specification instance to not.\n    12→   */\n    13→  public NotSpecification(Specification<T> spec1) {\n    14→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    20→    return !spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"0cd7cfa3-8151-4fda-9dec-bb2ae9b74c96"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ANf6cnPKWNUdk1ovA4iJsV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * Abstract base implementation of composite {@link Specification} with default implementations for\n     5→ * {@code and}, {@code or} and {@code not}.\n     6→ */\n     7→public abstract class AbstractSpecification<T> implements Specification<T> {\n     8→\n     9→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    10→  @Override\n    11→  public abstract boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t);\n    12→\n    13→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    14→  @Override\n    15→  public Specification<T> and(Specification<T> specification) {\n    16→    return new AndSpecification<>(this, specification);\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    20→  @Override\n    21→  public Specification<T> or(Specification<T> specification) {\n    22→    return new OrSpecification<>(this, specification);\n    23→  }\n    24→\n    25→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    26→  @Override\n    27→  public Specification<T> not(Specification<T> specification) {\n    28→    return new NotSpecification<>(specification);\n    29→  }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"18a9e948-234b-4388-a746-b658db95c7ca"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015j11Hzgr2Xo9BuPZrPw5hS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→// TODO [Clean Code] Make this a CDI singleton?\n     4→public class DomainObjectUtils {\n     5→\n     6→  /** Prevent instantiation. */\n     7→  private DomainObjectUtils() {}\n     8→\n     9→  /**\n    10→   * @param actual actual value\n    11→   * @param safe a null-safe value\n    12→   * @param <T> type\n    13→   * @return actual value, if it's not null, or safe value if the actual value is null.\n    14→   */\n    15→  public static <T> T nullSafe(T actual, T safe) {\n    16→    return actual == null ? safe : actual;\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"2b531bc0-ae2a-4b0b-a356-9948e7360ceb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Rdiu81YjygLDTr3pDFZM89","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n     6→\n     7→public interface RoutingService {\n     8→\n     9→  /**\n    10→   * @param routeSpecification Route specification\n    11→   * @return A list of itineraries that satisfy the specification. May be an empty list if no route\n    12→   *     is found.\n    13→   */\n    14→  List<Itinerary> fetchRoutesForSpecification(RouteSpecification routeSpecification);\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"19af9cc5-6de2-4123-a382-973ff778239a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Vi97cKV9h1GmoeZNEuTcPq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→\n     5→public interface VoyageRepository {\n     6→\n     7→  Voyage find(VoyageNumber voyageNumber);\n     8→\n     9→  List<Voyage> findAll();\n    10→}\n    11→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"4dc4d36e-d029-4de4-a6af-8fce2c21a3a0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018pwmbcTRttD2jMXt7bQ1yx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.logging;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import javax.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n     7→import javax.enterprise.inject.spi.InjectionPoint;\n     8→\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class LoggerProducer implements Serializable {\n    11→\n    12→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    13→\n    14→  @Produces\n    15→  public Logger produceLogger(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n    16→    String loggerName = extractLoggerName(injectionPoint);\n    17→\n    18→    return Logger.getLogger(loggerName);\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  private String extractLoggerName(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n    22→    if (injectionPoint.getBean() == null) {\n    23→      return injectionPoint.getMember().getDeclaringClass().getName();\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    if (injectionPoint.getBean().getName() == null) {\n    27→      return injectionPoint.getBean().getBeanClass().getName();\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    return injectionPoint.getBean().getName();\n    31→  }\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"e06334f2-2a6c-4355-98a3-5db124e2626a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014KxXaoYzDfkEewoj3NiQf2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.persistence.jpa;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.UUID;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     7→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     8→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→import javax.enterprise.event.Event;\n    10→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    11→import javax.persistence.EntityManager;\n    12→import javax.persistence.NoResultException;\n    13→import javax.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\n    18→\n    19→@ApplicationScoped\n    20→public class JpaCargoRepository implements CargoRepository, Serializable {\n    21→\n    22→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    23→\n    24→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    25→\n    26→  @PersistenceContext private EntityManager entityManager;\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject @CargoUpdated private Event<Cargo> cargoUpdated;\n    29→\n    30→  @Override\n    31→  public Cargo find(TrackingId trackingId) {\n    32→    Cargo cargo;\n    33→\n    34→    try {\n    35→      cargo =\n    36→          entityManager\n    37→              .createNamedQuery(\"Cargo.findByTrackingId\", Cargo.class)\n    38→              .setParameter(\"trackingId\", trackingId)\n    39→              .getSingleResult();\n    40→    } catch (NoResultException e) {\n    41→      logger.log(Level.FINE, \"Find called on non-existant tracking ID.\", e);\n    42→      cargo = null;\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    return cargo;\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  @Override\n    49→  public List<Cargo> findAll() {\n    50→    return entityManager.createNamedQuery(\"Cargo.findAll\", Cargo.class).getResultList();\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  @Override\n    54→  public void store(Cargo cargo) {\n    55→    // TODO [Clean Code] See why cascade is not working correctly for legs.\n    56→    cargo.getItinerary().getLegs().forEach(leg -> entityManager.persist(leg));\n    57→\n    58→    entityManager.persist(cargo);\n    59→\n    60→    cargoUpdated.fireAsync(cargo);\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  @Override\n    64→  public TrackingId nextTrackingId() {\n    65→    String random = UUID.randomUUID().toString().toUpperCase();\n    66→\n    67→    return new TrackingId(random.substring(0, random.indexOf(\"-\")));\n    68→  }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"a2db8bdb-8f87-4a1b-b0bf-f16695c3697f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DgepxqTsZyhgPStrau7pwu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import javax.ejb.ActivationConfigProperty;\n     6→import javax.ejb.MessageDriven;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import javax.jms.JMSException;\n     9→import javax.jms.Message;\n    10→import javax.jms.MessageListener;\n    11→\n    12→@MessageDriven(\n    13→    activationConfig = {\n    14→      @ActivationConfigProperty(\n    15→          propertyName = \"destinationType\",\n    16→          propertyValue = \"javax.jms.Queue\"),\n    17→      @ActivationConfigProperty(\n    18→          propertyName = \"destinationLookup\",\n    19→          propertyValue = \"java:app/jms/RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue\")\n    20→    })\n    21→public class RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer implements MessageListener {\n    22→\n    23→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    24→\n    25→  @Override\n    26→  public void onMessage(Message message) {\n    27→    try {\n    28→      logger.log(\n    29→          Level.INFO,\n    30→          \"Rejected registration attempt of cargo with tracking ID {0}.\",\n    31→          message.getBody(String.class));\n    32→    } catch (JMSException ex) {\n    33→      logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Error processing message.\", ex);\n    34→    }\n    35→  }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"ffa284c5-d098-4d3a-a982-227db3d5caba"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01J2jUx4zqsCRSUbvyvAPXAS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import javax.ejb.ActivationConfigProperty;\n     6→import javax.ejb.MessageDriven;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import javax.jms.JMSException;\n     9→import javax.jms.Message;\n    10→import javax.jms.MessageListener;\n    11→\n    12→@MessageDriven(\n    13→    activationConfig = {\n    14→      @ActivationConfigProperty(\n    15→          propertyName = \"destinationType\",\n    16→          propertyValue = \"javax.jms.Queue\"),\n    17→      @ActivationConfigProperty(\n    18→          propertyName = \"destinationLookup\",\n    19→          propertyValue = \"java:app/jms/MisdirectedCargoQueue\")\n    20→    })\n    21→public class MisdirectedCargoConsumer implements MessageListener {\n    22→\n    23→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    24→\n    25→  @Override\n    26→  public void onMessage(Message message) {\n    27→    try {\n    28→      logger.log(\n    29→          Level.INFO, \"Cargo with tracking ID {0} misdirected.\", message.getBody(String.class));\n    30→    } catch (JMSException ex) {\n    31→      logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Error processing message.\", ex);\n    32→    }\n    33→  }\n    34→}\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"7db87ebd-34f7-4643-b6b0-c141fa6fd2d6"}
