{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014RYf7nyBbf7xXzrNf5CT1F","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * At the moment, coordinates are effectively a shared DTO in the interface layer. It may be\n     5→ * converted to a domain level concern at some point. *\n     6→ */\n     7→public class Coordinates {\n     8→\n     9→  private final double latitude;\n    10→  private final double longitude;\n    11→\n    12→  public Coordinates(double latitude, double longitude) {\n    13→    this.latitude = latitude;\n    14→    this.longitude = longitude;\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  public double getLatitude() {\n    18→    return latitude;\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  public double getLongitude() {\n    22→    return longitude;\n    23→  }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"7342d9e3-6c22-4b07-a5df-7365b9701dcb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Rkp2CLrGfz5wqvsw8Cansv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location.UNKNOWN;\n     4→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.CHICAGO;\n     5→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.DALLAS;\n     6→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.GOTHENBURG;\n     7→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HAMBURG;\n     8→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HANGZOU;\n     9→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HELSINKI;\n    10→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HONGKONG;\n    11→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.MELBOURNE;\n    12→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.NEWYORK;\n    13→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM;\n    14→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.SHANGHAI;\n    15→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM;\n    16→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.TOKYO;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.Collections;\n    19→import java.util.HashMap;\n    20→import java.util.Map;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    23→\n    24→/**\n    25→ * At the moment, coordinates are produced by a simple factory. It may be converted to a repository\n    26→ * if coordinates become a domain layer concern.\n    27→ */\n    28→public class CoordinatesFactory {\n    29→\n    30→  private static final Map<String, Coordinates> COORDINATES_MAP;\n    31→\n    32→  private CoordinatesFactory() {\n    33→    /* Prevent instantiation. */\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public static Coordinates find(Location location) {\n    37→    return find(location.getUnLocode());\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public static Coordinates find(UnLocode unLocode) {\n    41→    return find(unLocode.getIdString());\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public static Coordinates find(String unLocode) {\n    45→    return COORDINATES_MAP.get(unLocode);\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  static {\n    49→    Map<String, Coordinates> map = new HashMap<>();\n    50→\n    51→    // TODO [Clean Code] See if there is a service to get the latitude/longitude data from.\n    52→    map.put(HONGKONG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(22, 114));\n    53→    map.put(MELBOURNE.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(-38, 145));\n    54→    map.put(STOCKHOLM.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(59, 18));\n    55→    map.put(HELSINKI.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(60, 25));\n    56→    map.put(CHICAGO.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(42, -88));\n    57→    map.put(TOKYO.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(36, 140));\n    58→    map.put(HAMBURG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(54, 10));\n    59→    map.put(SHANGHAI.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(31, 121));\n    60→    map.put(ROTTERDAM.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(52, 5));\n    61→    map.put(GOTHENBURG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(58, 12));\n    62→    map.put(HANGZOU.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(30, 120));\n    63→    map.put(NEWYORK.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(41, -74));\n    64→    map.put(DALLAS.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(33, -97));\n    65→    map.put(UNKNOWN.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(-90, 0)); // The South Pole.\n    66→\n    67→    COORDINATES_MAP = Collections.unmodifiableMap(map);\n    68→  }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"31213da7-c37c-4d7a-ac65-5e326f852a4b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017AVtEJRb4sgyJt5SGcFDk8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.routing;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     7→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     8→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     9→import javax.annotation.Resource;\n    10→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n    11→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    12→import javax.ws.rs.client.ClientBuilder;\n    13→import javax.ws.rs.client.WebTarget;\n    14→import javax.ws.rs.core.GenericType;\n    15→import javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    23→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service.RoutingService;\n    24→import org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitEdge;\n    25→import org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitPath;\n    26→\n    27→/**\n    28→ * Our end of the routing service. This is basically a data model translation layer between our\n    29→ * domain model and the API put forward by the routing team, which operates in a different context\n    30→ * from us.\n    31→ */\n    32→@Stateless\n    33→public class ExternalRoutingService implements RoutingService {\n    34→\n    35→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    36→\n    37→  @Resource(lookup = \"java:app/configuration/GraphTraversalUrl\")\n    38→  private String graphTraversalUrl;\n    39→\n    40→  private WebTarget graphTraversalResource;\n    41→\n    42→  @Inject private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    43→  @Inject private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    44→\n    45→  @PostConstruct\n    46→  public void init() {\n    47→    graphTraversalResource = ClientBuilder.newClient().target(graphTraversalUrl);\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  @Override\n    51→  public List<Itinerary> fetchRoutesForSpecification(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n    52→    // The RouteSpecification is picked apart and adapted to the external API.\n    53→    String origin = routeSpecification.getOrigin().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n    54→    String destination = routeSpecification.getDestination().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n    55→\n    56→    List<TransitPath> transitPaths =\n    57→        graphTraversalResource\n    58→            .queryParam(\"origin\", origin)\n    59→            .queryParam(\"destination\", destination)\n    60→            .request(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_TYPE)\n    61→            .get(new GenericType<List<TransitPath>>() {});\n    62→\n    63→    // The returned result is then translated back into our domain model.\n    64→    List<Itinerary> itineraries = new ArrayList<>();\n    65→\n    66→    // Use the specification to safe-guard against invalid itineraries\n    67→    transitPaths\n    68→        .stream()\n    69→        .map(this::toItinerary)\n    70→        .forEach(\n    71→            itinerary -> {\n    72→              if (routeSpecification.isSatisfiedBy(itinerary)) {\n    73→                itineraries.add(itinerary);\n    74→              } else {\n    75→                logger.log(\n    76→                    Level.FINE, \"Received itinerary that did not satisfy the route specification\");\n    77→              }\n    78→            });\n    79→\n    80→    return itineraries;\n    81→  }\n    82→\n    83→  private Itinerary toItinerary(TransitPath transitPath) {\n    84→    List<Leg> legs =\n    85→        transitPath.getTransitEdges().stream().map(this::toLeg).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    86→    return new Itinerary(legs);\n    87→  }\n    88→\n    89→  private Leg toLeg(TransitEdge edge) {\n    90→    return new Leg(\n    91→        voyageRepository.find(new VoyageNumber(edge.getVoyageNumber())),\n    92→        locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getFromUnLocode())),\n    93→        locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getToUnLocode())),\n    94→        edge.getFromDate(),\n    95→        edge.getToDate());\n    96→  }\n    97→}\n    98→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"e456cbda-a0e9-4b44-bd8c-98ba7416a6cd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EDhStY8zG7CpMWob6SoC2G","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.persistence.jpa;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import javax.persistence.EntityManager;\n     7→import javax.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class JpaVoyageRepository implements VoyageRepository, Serializable {\n    14→\n    15→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    16→\n    17→  @PersistenceContext private EntityManager entityManager;\n    18→\n    19→  @Override\n    20→  public Voyage find(VoyageNumber voyageNumber) {\n    21→    return entityManager\n    22→        .createNamedQuery(\"Voyage.findByVoyageNumber\", Voyage.class)\n    23→        .setParameter(\"voyageNumber\", voyageNumber)\n    24→        .getSingleResult();\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  @Override\n    28→  public List<Voyage> findAll() {\n    29→    return entityManager.createNamedQuery(\"Voyage.findAll\", Voyage.class).getResultList();\n    30→  }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"e98d0883-4040-4d47-a04f-525d7e7b9c12"}
