{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019eVLMTRLv6y9byqYQoxCfS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.persistence.jpa;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import javax.persistence.EntityManager;\n     7→import javax.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class JpaLocationRepository implements LocationRepository, Serializable {\n    14→\n    15→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    16→\n    17→  @PersistenceContext private EntityManager entityManager;\n    18→\n    19→  @Override\n    20→  public Location find(UnLocode unLocode) {\n    21→    return entityManager\n    22→        .createNamedQuery(\"Location.findByUnLocode\", Location.class)\n    23→        .setParameter(\"unLocode\", unLocode)\n    24→        .getSingleResult();\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  @Override\n    28→  public List<Location> findAll() {\n    29→    return entityManager.createNamedQuery(\"Location.findAll\", Location.class).getResultList();\n    30→  }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"6ee0ebf9-4fb5-4f89-ba5b-d6fec6dea138"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01V3p3L1zzcVyJJnDzYm4Mce","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.persistence.jpa;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import javax.persistence.EntityManager;\n     6→import javax.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class JpaHandlingEventRepository implements HandlingEventRepository, Serializable {\n    14→\n    15→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    16→\n    17→  @PersistenceContext private EntityManager entityManager;\n    18→\n    19→  @Override\n    20→  public void store(HandlingEvent event) {\n    21→    entityManager.persist(event);\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  @Override\n    25→  public HandlingHistory lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(TrackingId trackingId) {\n    26→    return new HandlingHistory(\n    27→        entityManager\n    28→            .createNamedQuery(\"HandlingEvent.findByTrackingId\", HandlingEvent.class)\n    29→            .setParameter(\"trackingId\", trackingId)\n    30→            .getResultList());\n    31→  }\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WD9HU4zfz66rKcFfgrdxib","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-