{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UFU5uwSJ5Qa3SytXQyECYD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully read all the requested files. Let me now provide a comprehensive summary with all the complete source code.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Source Code for All Requested Files\n\nI have successfully retrieved all 32 Java files and 1 SQL file. Below is the complete source code for each file:\n\n### 1. Cargo.java\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Cargo.java`\n\nThe file contains 194 lines of code defining the central Cargo entity class with JPA annotations, tracking ID, origin, route specification, itinerary, and delivery management.\n\n### 2. Delivery.java\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Delivery.java`\n\nContains 383 lines implementing the Delivery embeddable class that tracks cargo transportation status, including transport status, routing status, location, voyage, ETA, and delivery calculations.\n\n### 3. Itinerary.java\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Itinerary.java`\n\n167 lines defining the Itinerary embeddable class with a list of Legs, including validation logic for handling events.\n\n### 4. Leg.java\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Leg.java`\n\n147 lines defining a Leg entity representing a single segment of