{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LZ9DPLyG1aiaLqNncBCVhS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01QYvfZjrAELQ8epaxEvmqkL","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Create Spring Boot config files","prompt":"Create the following files for the Spring Boot migration of the Cargo Tracker application. The base directory is /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\n\n1. Create file: src/main/resources/application.properties with:\n```\n# Spring Boot Application Configuration\nserver.port=8080\nserver.servlet.context-path=/cargo-tracker\n\n# H2 Database\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:cargotracker;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\nspring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\nspring.datasource.username=sa\nspring.datasource.password=\n\n# JPA / Hibernate\nspring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.properties.hibernate.format_sql=true\n\n# H2 Console (for development)\nspring.h2.console.enabled=true\nspring.h2.console.path=/h2-console\n\n# Logging\nlogging.level.org.eclipse.cargotracker=INFO\nlogging.level.org.springframework=INFO\n\n# Application Settings\napp.graphTraversalUrl=http://localhost:8080/cargo-tracker/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path\n```\n\n2. Create file: src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/CargoTrackerApplication.java with:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.ComponentScan;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableScheduling;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@EnableScheduling\n@ComponentScan(basePackages = {\"org.eclipse.cargotracker\", \"org.eclipse.pathfinder\"})\npublic class CargoTrackerApplication {\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(CargoTrackerApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n3. Move/keep the SQL file at: src/main/resources/data.sql (Spring Boot will auto-execute this)\nWrite this file with content:\n```sql\nINSERT INTO applicationsettings (id, sampleloaded) VALUES (1, FALSE);\n```\n\nPlease use the Write tool to create all three files.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":409,"cache_read_input_tokens":106977,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":409,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4472},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"d249a0e9-490a-45e1-8e62-b5b5002cbd94"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LZ9DPLyG1aiaLqNncBCVhS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01RrpJLRCoFFqjVdDtQrqPpK","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate domain model classes","prompt":"Migrate the domain model Java classes from Jakarta EE (javax.*) to Spring Boot. The base directory is /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\n\nFor ALL domain model files, the main change is replacing javax.persistence.* with javax.persistence.* (Spring Boot 2.7.x still uses javax.persistence, NOT jakarta.persistence). Also javax.validation.* stays as javax.validation.* in Spring Boot 2.7.x.\n\nThe domain model files that need changes are primarily the JPA entities and embeddables. Since Spring Boot 2.7.x still uses javax.* namespace, most domain model files should remain the same or need minimal changes.\n\nHere's the key mapping:\n- javax.persistence.* -> STAYS as javax.persistence.* (Spring Boot 2.7 uses Hibernate 5 with javax)\n- javax.validation.* -> STAYS as javax.validation.* \n- javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped -> org.springframework.stereotype.Component (only for CDI beans)\n- javax.inject.Inject -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired\n- javax.inject.Qualifier -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier\n\nFILES TO UPDATE (only update files that actually use CDI/EJB annotations):\n\n1. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEventFactory.java\n   - Replace: javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped -> org.springframework.stereotype.Component\n   - Replace: javax.inject.Inject -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired\n   - Keep javax.persistence.* and domain imports unchanged\n\nThe following domain files should NOT need changes since they only use javax.persistence.* which is still valid in Spring Boot 2.7.x:\n- All Entity/Embeddable classes (Cargo, Delivery, Itinerary, Leg, etc.)\n- All value objects (TrackingId, VoyageNumber, UnLocode, etc.)\n- All repository interfaces (CargoRepository, etc.)\n- All enums (TransportStatus, RoutingStatus, etc.)\n- All exception classes\n- All specification classes\n- All utility classes without CDI\n\nHowever, please READ HandlingEventFactory.java first to confirm the exact imports, then use Edit to update it.\n\nWrite the updated HandlingEventFactory.java using the Edit tool.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":409,"cache_read_input_tokens":106977,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":409,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4472},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"cc5f42dc-e3c7-4376-803d-a84c9f19d449"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LZ9DPLyG1aiaLqNncBCVhS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01TKdeqLm4bzocmSU7PWw7jH","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate infrastructure persistence","prompt":"Migrate the JPA repository implementations from Jakarta EE CDI/EJB to Spring Boot. The base directory is /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\n\nFor each file, READ the file first, then use Edit to make changes.\n\nChanges needed for ALL JPA repository files:\n- Replace: javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped -> org.springframework.stereotype.Repository\n- Replace: javax.inject.Inject -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired\n- Replace: javax.persistence.PersistenceContext -> javax.persistence.PersistenceContext (keep as is)\n- Replace: javax.enterprise.event.Event -> remove (will use Spring events instead)\n- Replace: javax.enterprise.inject.Produces -> remove\n- Keep: javax.persistence.* imports unchanged\n\nFiles to update:\n\n1. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaCargoRepository.java\n   - Change @ApplicationScoped to @Repository\n   - Change @Inject to @Autowired  \n   - Replace CDI Event<Cargo> with Spring ApplicationEventPublisher\n   - Replace @CargoUpdated qualifier with Spring event publishing\n   - Add: import org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher;\n   - Add: import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\n   - Add: import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n   - Add @Transactional to store method: import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n   - The cargoUpdated.fireAsync(cargo) should become applicationEventPublisher.publishEvent(cargo);\n\n2. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaVoyageRepository.java\n   - Change @ApplicationScoped to @Repository\n   - Keep @PersistenceContext unchanged\n\n3. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaLocationRepository.java\n   - Change @ApplicationScoped to @Repository\n   - Keep @PersistenceContext unchanged\n\n4. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaHandlingEventRepository.java\n   - Change @ApplicationScoped to @Repository\n   - Keep @PersistenceContext unchanged\n\nAlso update:\n5. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/events/cdi/CargoUpdated.java\n   - This CDI qualifier annotation is no longer needed. Replace the entire file content with a simple marker annotation or Spring event class. Make it a simple empty class file that other code can reference:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi;\n\n/**\n * Marker annotation - in Spring Boot, CDI events are replaced by Spring ApplicationEvents.\n * This class is kept for reference but is no longer used as a CDI qualifier.\n */\npublic @interface CargoUpdated {}\n```\n\nPlease read each file first, then edit them.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":409,"cache_read_input_tokens":106977,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":409,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4472},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"9c0707b0-a01f-4c82-9609-ce552135dcc6"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LZ9DPLyG1aiaLqNncBCVhS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01K9FwxYA4GWcNpL84p8uJxo","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate application services","prompt":"Migrate the application services from Jakarta EE EJB to Spring Boot. The base directory is /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\n\nFor each file, READ the file first, then use Edit to make changes.\n\nKey mappings:\n- @Stateless -> @Service + @Transactional\n- @Singleton @Startup -> @Component (with @PostConstruct and @EventListener)\n- @Inject -> @Autowired\n- @PersistenceContext -> @PersistenceContext (stays)\n- @TransactionAttribute -> @Transactional\n- javax.ejb.* -> remove/replace with Spring equivalents\n- javax.inject.Inject -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired\n- javax.annotation.PostConstruct -> javax.annotation.PostConstruct (stays in Spring Boot 2.7)\n\nFiles to update:\n\n1. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultHandlingEventService.java\n   - Replace: @Stateless with @Service and @Transactional\n   - Replace: @Inject with @Autowired\n   - Replace javax.ejb.Stateless import with org.springframework.stereotype.Service\n   - Add: import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n\n2. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultBookingService.java\n   - Same changes as above\n\n3. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultCargoInspectionService.java\n   - Same changes as above\n\n4. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/SampleDataGenerator.java\n   - Replace: @Singleton @Startup with @Component\n   - Replace: @Inject with @Autowired\n   - Replace: @PersistenceContext stays\n   - Replace: @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED) with @Transactional\n   - Keep: @PostConstruct (from javax.annotation.PostConstruct - still valid)\n   - Remove: javax.ejb.* imports\n   - Add: import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n   - Add: import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n   - Add: import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n\n5. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/RestConfiguration.java\n   - This JAX-RS configuration class is no longer needed in Spring Boot.\n   - Replace the entire content with an empty/stub class that won't interfere:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n\n/**\n * REST configuration - in Spring Boot, REST is configured automatically.\n * This class is no longer needed as Spring Boot auto-configures REST endpoints.\n */\npublic class RestConfiguration {\n    // No longer needed - Spring Boot auto-configures REST\n}\n```\n\n6. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/ApplicationSettings.java\n   - Keep as is (it's a plain JPA @Entity with javax.persistence annotations, valid in Spring Boot 2.7)\n\n7. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/logging/LoggerProducer.java\n   - This CDI producer is no longer needed. Replace with a Spring configuration:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.logging;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.InjectionPoint;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Scope;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class LoggerProducer {\n\n    @Bean\n    @Scope(\"prototype\")\n    public Logger produceLogger(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n        Class<?> declaringClass = injectionPoint.getMember().getDeclaringClass();\n        return Logger.getLogger(declaringClass.getName());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n8. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/routing/ExternalRoutingService.java\n   - Replace: @Stateless with @Service\n   - Replace: @Inject with @Autowired  \n   - Replace: @Resource(lookup = \"java:app/configuration/GraphTraversalUrl\") with @Value(\"${app.graphTraversalUrl}\")\n   - Replace: JAX-RS Client (javax.ws.rs.client.*) with Spring RestTemplate\n   - Keep: @PostConstruct\n   - The graphTraversalResource should use Spring's RestTemplate instead of JAX-RS Client\n\nReplace the full file with:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.routing;\n\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service.RoutingService;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitEdge;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitPath;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;\nimport org.springframework.core.ParameterizedTypeReference;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpMethod;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\nimport org.springframework.web.client.RestTemplate;\nimport org.springframework.web.util.UriComponentsBuilder;\n\n@Service\npublic class ExternalRoutingService implements RoutingService {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private Logger logger;\n\n    @Value(\"${app.graphTraversalUrl}\")\n    private String graphTraversalUrl;\n\n    @Autowired\n    private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n\n    @Autowired\n    private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n\n    private RestTemplate restTemplate;\n\n    @PostConstruct\n    public void init() {\n        restTemplate = new RestTemplate();\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public List<Itinerary> fetchRoutesForSpecification(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n        String origin = routeSpecification.getOrigin().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n        String destination = routeSpecification.getDestination().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n\n        String url = UriComponentsBuilder.fromHttpUrl(graphTraversalUrl)\n                .queryParam(\"origin\", origin)\n                .queryParam(\"destination\", destination)\n                .toUriString();\n\n        ResponseEntity<List<TransitPath>> response = restTemplate.exchange(\n                url,\n                HttpMethod.GET,\n                null,\n                new ParameterizedTypeReference<List<TransitPath>>() {});\n\n        List<TransitPath> transitPaths = response.getBody();\n\n        List<Itinerary> itineraries = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        if (transitPaths != null) {\n            transitPaths.stream()\n                    .map(this::toItinerary)\n                    .forEach(itinerary -> {\n                        if (routeSpecification.isSatisfiedBy(itinerary)) {\n                            itineraries.add(itinerary);\n                        } else {\n                            logger.log(Level.FINE,\n                                    \"Received itinerary that did not satisfy the route specification\");\n                        }\n                    });\n        }\n\n        return itineraries;\n    }\n\n    private Itinerary toItinerary(TransitPath transitPath) {\n        List<Leg> legs = transitPath.getTransitEdges().stream()\n                .map(this::toLeg)\n                .collect(Collectors.toList());\n        return new Itinerary(legs);\n    }\n\n    private Leg toLeg(TransitEdge edge) {\n        return new Leg(\n                voyageRepository.find(new VoyageNumber(edge.getVoyageNumber())),\n                locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getFromUnLocode())),\n                locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getToUnLocode())),\n                edge.getFromDate(),\n                edge.getToDate());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nPlease read each file first, then edit/write them.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":409,"cache_read_input_tokens":106977,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":409,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4472},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"8343c968-1ba9-44a5-aced-4e64e3a099aa"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Create the following files for the Spring Boot migration of the Cargo Tracker application. The base directory is /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\n\n1. Create file: src/main/resources/application.properties with:\n```\n# Spring Boot Application Configuration\nserver.port=8080\nserver.servlet.context-path=/cargo-tracker\n\n# H2 Database\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:cargotracker;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\nspring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\nspring.datasource.username=sa\nspring.datasource.password=\n\n# JPA / Hibernate\nspring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.properties.hibernate.format_sql=true\n\n# H2 Console (for development)\nspring.h2.console.enabled=true\nspring.h2.console.path=/h2-console\n\n# Logging\nlogging.level.org.eclipse.cargotracker=INFO\nlogging.level.org.springframework=INFO\n\n# Application Settings\napp.graphTraversalUrl=http://localhost:8080/cargo-tracker/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path\n```\n\n2. Create file: src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/CargoTrackerApplication.java with:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.ComponentScan;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableScheduling;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@EnableScheduling\n@ComponentScan(basePackages = {\"org.eclipse.cargotracker\", \"org.eclipse.pathfinder\"})\npublic class CargoTrackerApplication {\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(CargoTrackerApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n3. Move/keep the SQL file at: src/main/resources/data.sql (Spring Boot will auto-execute this)\nWrite this file with content:\n```sql\nINSERT INTO applicationsettings (id, sampleloaded) VALUES (1, FALSE);\n```\n\nPlease use the Write tool to create all three files."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QYvfZjrAELQ8epaxEvmqkL","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"8a694c7f-e1b9-4d68-a80c-586249c03af5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Migrate the domain model Java classes from Jakarta EE (javax.*) to Spring Boot. The base directory is /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\n\nFor ALL domain model files, the main change is replacing javax.persistence.* with javax.persistence.* (Spring Boot 2.7.x still uses javax.persistence, NOT jakarta.persistence). Also javax.validation.* stays as javax.validation.* in Spring Boot 2.7.x.\n\nThe domain model files that need changes are primarily the JPA entities and embeddables. Since Spring Boot 2.7.x still uses javax.* namespace, most domain model files should remain the same or need minimal changes.\n\nHere's the key mapping:\n- javax.persistence.* -> STAYS as javax.persistence.* (Spring Boot 2.7 uses Hibernate 5 with javax)\n- javax.validation.* -> STAYS as javax.validation.* \n- javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped -> org.springframework.stereotype.Component (only for CDI beans)\n- javax.inject.Inject -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired\n- javax.inject.Qualifier -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier\n\nFILES TO UPDATE (only update files that actually use CDI/EJB annotations):\n\n1. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEventFactory.java\n   - Replace: javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped -> org.springframework.stereotype.Component\n   - Replace: javax.inject.Inject -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired\n   - Keep javax.persistence.* and domain imports unchanged\n\nThe following domain files should NOT need changes since they only use javax.persistence.* which is still valid in Spring Boot 2.7.x:\n- All Entity/Embeddable classes (Cargo, Delivery, Itinerary, Leg, etc.)\n- All value objects (TrackingId, VoyageNumber, UnLocode, etc.)\n- All repository interfaces (CargoRepository, etc.)\n- All enums (TransportStatus, RoutingStatus, etc.)\n- All exception classes\n- All specification classes\n- All utility classes without CDI\n\nHowever, please READ HandlingEventFactory.java first to confirm the exact imports, then use Edit to update it.\n\nWrite the updated HandlingEventFactory.java using the Edit tool."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RrpJLRCoFFqjVdDtQrqPpK","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"7e47aaa2-e3fe-4ea8-a04a-d775469f9d39"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Migrate the JPA repository implementations from Jakarta EE CDI/EJB to Spring Boot. The base directory is /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\n\nFor each file, READ the file first, then use Edit to make changes.\n\nChanges needed for ALL JPA repository files:\n- Replace: javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped -> org.springframework.stereotype.Repository\n- Replace: javax.inject.Inject -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired\n- Replace: javax.persistence.PersistenceContext -> javax.persistence.PersistenceContext (keep as is)\n- Replace: javax.enterprise.event.Event -> remove (will use Spring events instead)\n- Replace: javax.enterprise.inject.Produces -> remove\n- Keep: javax.persistence.* imports unchanged\n\nFiles to update:\n\n1. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaCargoRepository.java\n   - Change @ApplicationScoped to @Repository\n   - Change @Inject to @Autowired  \n   - Replace CDI Event<Cargo> with Spring ApplicationEventPublisher\n   - Replace @CargoUpdated qualifier with Spring event publishing\n   - Add: import org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher;\n   - Add: import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\n   - Add: import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n   - Add @Transactional to store method: import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n   - The cargoUpdated.fireAsync(cargo) should become applicationEventPublisher.publishEvent(cargo);\n\n2. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaVoyageRepository.java\n   - Change @ApplicationScoped to @Repository\n   - Keep @PersistenceContext unchanged\n\n3. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaLocationRepository.java\n   - Change @ApplicationScoped to @Repository\n   - Keep @PersistenceContext unchanged\n\n4. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaHandlingEventRepository.java\n   - Change @ApplicationScoped to @Repository\n   - Keep @PersistenceContext unchanged\n\nAlso update:\n5. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/events/cdi/CargoUpdated.java\n   - This CDI qualifier annotation is no longer needed. Replace the entire file content with a simple marker annotation or Spring event class. Make it a simple empty class file that other code can reference:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi;\n\n/**\n * Marker annotation - in Spring Boot, CDI events are replaced by Spring ApplicationEvents.\n * This class is kept for reference but is no longer used as a CDI qualifier.\n */\npublic @interface CargoUpdated {}\n```\n\nPlease read each file first, then edit them."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TKdeqLm4bzocmSU7PWw7jH","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"045b5007-6df2-46b6-aba7-85144e9f94f7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Migrate the application services from Jakarta EE EJB to Spring Boot. The base directory is /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\n\nFor each file, READ the file first, then use Edit to make changes.\n\nKey mappings:\n- @Stateless -> @Service + @Transactional\n- @Singleton @Startup -> @Component (with @PostConstruct and @EventListener)\n- @Inject -> @Autowired\n- @PersistenceContext -> @PersistenceContext (stays)\n- @TransactionAttribute -> @Transactional\n- javax.ejb.* -> remove/replace with Spring equivalents\n- javax.inject.Inject -> org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired\n- javax.annotation.PostConstruct -> javax.annotation.PostConstruct (stays in Spring Boot 2.7)\n\nFiles to update:\n\n1. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultHandlingEventService.java\n   - Replace: @Stateless with @Service and @Transactional\n   - Replace: @Inject with @Autowired\n   - Replace javax.ejb.Stateless import with org.springframework.stereotype.Service\n   - Add: import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n\n2. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultBookingService.java\n   - Same changes as above\n\n3. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultCargoInspectionService.java\n   - Same changes as above\n\n4. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/SampleDataGenerator.java\n   - Replace: @Singleton @Startup with @Component\n   - Replace: @Inject with @Autowired\n   - Replace: @PersistenceContext stays\n   - Replace: @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED) with @Transactional\n   - Keep: @PostConstruct (from javax.annotation.PostConstruct - still valid)\n   - Remove: javax.ejb.* imports\n   - Add: import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n   - Add: import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n   - Add: import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n\n5. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/RestConfiguration.java\n   - This JAX-RS configuration class is no longer needed in Spring Boot.\n   - Replace the entire content with an empty/stub class that won't interfere:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n\n/**\n * REST configuration - in Spring Boot, REST is configured automatically.\n * This class is no longer needed as Spring Boot auto-configures REST endpoints.\n */\npublic class RestConfiguration {\n    // No longer needed - Spring Boot auto-configures REST\n}\n```\n\n6. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/ApplicationSettings.java\n   - Keep as is (it's a plain JPA @Entity with javax.persistence annotations, valid in Spring Boot 2.7)\n\n7. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/logging/LoggerProducer.java\n   - This CDI producer is no longer needed. Replace with a Spring configuration:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.logging;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.InjectionPoint;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Scope;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class LoggerProducer {\n\n    @Bean\n    @Scope(\"prototype\")\n    public Logger produceLogger(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {\n        Class<?> declaringClass = injectionPoint.getMember().getDeclaringClass();\n        return Logger.getLogger(declaringClass.getName());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n8. src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/routing/ExternalRoutingService.java\n   - Replace: @Stateless with @Service\n   - Replace: @Inject with @Autowired  \n   - Replace: @Resource(lookup = \"java:app/configuration/GraphTraversalUrl\") with @Value(\"${app.graphTraversalUrl}\")\n   - Replace: JAX-RS Client (javax.ws.rs.client.*) with Spring RestTemplate\n   - Keep: @PostConstruct\n   - The graphTraversalResource should use Spring's RestTemplate instead of JAX-RS Client\n\nReplace the full file with:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.routing;\n\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service.RoutingService;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitEdge;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitPath;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;\nimport org.springframework.core.ParameterizedTypeReference;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpMethod;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\nimport org.springframework.web.client.RestTemplate;\nimport org.springframework.web.util.UriComponentsBuilder;\n\n@Service\npublic class ExternalRoutingService implements RoutingService {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private Logger logger;\n\n    @Value(\"${app.graphTraversalUrl}\")\n    private String graphTraversalUrl;\n\n    @Autowired\n    private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n\n    @Autowired\n    private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n\n    private RestTemplate restTemplate;\n\n    @PostConstruct\n    public void init() {\n        restTemplate = new RestTemplate();\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public List<Itinerary> fetchRoutesForSpecification(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n        String origin = routeSpecification.getOrigin().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n        String destination = routeSpecification.getDestination().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n\n        String url = UriComponentsBuilder.fromHttpUrl(graphTraversalUrl)\n                .queryParam(\"origin\", origin)\n                .queryParam(\"destination\", destination)\n                .toUriString();\n\n        ResponseEntity<List<TransitPath>> response = restTemplate.exchange(\n                url,\n                HttpMethod.GET,\n                null,\n                new ParameterizedTypeReference<List<TransitPath>>() {});\n\n        List<TransitPath> transitPaths = response.getBody();\n\n        List<Itinerary> itineraries = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        if (transitPaths != null) {\n            transitPaths.stream()\n                    .map(this::toItinerary)\n                    .forEach(itinerary -> {\n                        if (routeSpecification.isSatisfiedBy(itinerary)) {\n                            itineraries.add(itinerary);\n                        } else {\n                            logger.log(Level.FINE,\n                                    \"Received itinerary that did not satisfy the route specification\");\n                        }\n                    });\n        }\n\n        return itineraries;\n    }\n\n    private Itinerary toItinerary(TransitPath transitPath) {\n        List<Leg> legs = transitPath.getTransitEdges().stream()\n                .map(this::toLeg)\n                .collect(Collectors.toList());\n        return new Itinerary(legs);\n    }\n\n    private Leg toLeg(TransitEdge edge) {\n        return new Leg(\n                voyageRepository.find(new VoyageNumber(edge.getVoyageNumber())),\n                locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getFromUnLocode())),\n                locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getToUnLocode())),\n                edge.getFromDate(),\n                edge.getToDate());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nPlease read each file first, then edit/write them."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01K9FwxYA4GWcNpL84p8uJxo","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"45f81328-3b9c-4e98-aa2c-b27c5a4d10ac"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_015WVToFswPpxfLp4YzHcXnZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01WBXNJWf81Pxm4wSaPFAa1h","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEventFactory.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":906,"cache_read_input_tokens":11008,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":906,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":166},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RrpJLRCoFFqjVdDtQrqPpK","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"d1a97732-3178-4d96-b268-923a34f2b817"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WBXNJWf81Pxm4wSaPFAa1h","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    16→\n    17→@ApplicationScoped\n    18→public class HandlingEventFactory implements Serializable {\n    19→\n    20→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    21→\n    22→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    23→  @Inject private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    24→  @Inject private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    25→\n    26→  /**\n    27→   * @param registrationTime time when this event was received by the system\n    28→   * @param completionTime when the event was completed, for example finished loading\n    29→   * @param trackingId cargo tracking id\n    30→   * @param voyageNumber voyage number\n    31→   * @param unlocode United Nations Location Code for the location of the event\n    32→   * @param type type of event\n    33→   * @return A handling event.\n    34→   * @throws UnknownVoyageException if there's no voyage with this number\n    35→   * @throws UnknownCargoException if there's no cargo with this tracking id\n    36→   * @throws UnknownLocationException if there's no location with this UN Locode\n    37→   */\n    38→  // TODO [Clean Code] Look at the exception handling more seriously.\n    39→  public HandlingEvent createHandlingEvent(\n    40→      LocalDateTime registrationTime,\n    41→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    42→      TrackingId trackingId,\n    43→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    44→      UnLocode unlocode,\n    45→      HandlingEvent.Type type)\n    46→      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n    47→    Cargo cargo = findCargo(trackingId);\n    48→    Voyage voyage = findVoyage(voyageNumber);\n    49→    Location location = findLocation(unlocode);\n    50→\n    51→    try {\n    52→      if (voyage == null) {\n    53→        return new HandlingEvent(cargo, completionTime, registrationTime, type, location);\n    54→      } else {\n    55→        return new HandlingEvent(cargo, completionTime, registrationTime, type, location, voyage);\n    56→      }\n    57→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    58→      throw new CannotCreateHandlingEventException(e);\n    59→    }\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  private Cargo findCargo(TrackingId trackingId) throws UnknownCargoException {\n    63→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    64→\n    65→    if (cargo == null) {\n    66→      throw new UnknownCargoException(trackingId);\n    67→    }\n    68→\n    69→    return cargo;\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  private Voyage findVoyage(VoyageNumber voyageNumber) throws UnknownVoyageException {\n    73→    if (voyageNumber == null) {\n    74→      return null;\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→    Voyage voyage = voyageRepository.find(voyageNumber);\n    78→\n    79→    if (voyage == null) {\n    80→      throw new UnknownVoyageException(voyageNumber);\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    return voyage;\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  private Location findLocation(UnLocode unlocode) throws UnknownLocationException {\n    87→    Location location = locationRepository.find(unlocode);\n    88→\n    89→    if (location == null) {\n    90→      throw new UnknownLocationException(unlocode);\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    return location;\n    94→  }\n    95→}\n    96→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RrpJLRCoFFqjVdDtQrqPpK","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"b4b844ae-a5ab-4ea6-8875-7ac7a9ba840b"}
