{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QYvfZjrAELQ8epaxEvmqkL","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three files have been successfully created for the Spring Boot migration:\n\n## Files Created:\n\n### 1. `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/resources/application.properties`\nThis file contains the Spring Boot application configuration including:\n- Server configuration (port 8080, context path /cargo-tracker)\n- H2 in-memory database configuration\n- JPA/Hibernate settings with auto-DDL schema creation\n- H2 console enabled for development\n- Logging configuration\n- Application-specific settings for the graph traversal URL\n\n### 2. `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/CargoTrackerApplication.java`\nThe main Spring Boot application class with:\n- `@SpringBootApplication` annotation for auto-configuration\n- `@EnableScheduling` to enable scheduled tasks\n- `@ComponentScan` for both cargotracker and pathfinder packages\n- Standard Spring Boot main method to launch the application\n\n### 3. `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/resources/data.sql`\nSQL initialization script that:\n- Will be automatically executed by Spring Boot on startup\n- Initializes the applicationsettings table with sampleloaded set to FALSE\n\nThese files provide the foundation for running the Cargo Tracker application as a Spring Boot application with an H2 in-memory database."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"53ead8c2-c657-437a-a0bd-1eb1e368d956"}
