{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_019vCo9pkysWqzAkAL3EF5z7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01YBEtRpPhQjBWT7fJA28LVM","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/sse/RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3953,"cache_read_input_tokens":11008,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3953,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":694},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KVSuvnVZ36J4NuwGNUF7jY","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"db7ca9df-ba1d-4b31-884a-cf0b2cab94a1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NsDNrrKCQtZiEJ4yCoeFxt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.rest;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n     5→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     6→import javax.validation.Valid;\n     7→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     8→import javax.ws.rs.Consumes;\n     9→import javax.ws.rs.POST;\n    10→import javax.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n    18→\n    19→/**\n    20→ * This REST end-point implementation performs basic validation and parsing of incoming data, and in\n    21→ * case of a valid registration attempt, sends an asynchronous message with the information to the\n    22→ * handling event registration system for proper registration.\n    23→ */\n    24→@Stateless\n    25→@Path(\"/handling\")\n    26→public class HandlingReportService {\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    29→\n    30→  @POST\n    31→  @Path(\"/reports\")\n    32→  @Consumes({\"application/json\", \"application/xml\"})\n    33→  public void submitReport(\n    34→      @NotNull(message = \"Missing handling report.\") @Valid HandlingReport handlingReport) {\n    35→    LocalDateTime completionTime = DateConverter.toDateTime(handlingReport.getCompletionTime());\n    36→    VoyageNumber voyageNumber = null;\n    37→\n    38→    if (handlingReport.getVoyageNumber() != null) {\n    39→      voyageNumber = new VoyageNumber(handlingReport.getVoyageNumber());\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    HandlingEvent.Type type = HandlingEvent.Type.valueOf(handlingReport.getEventType());\n    43→    UnLocode unLocode = new UnLocode(handlingReport.getUnLocode());\n    44→\n    45→    TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(handlingReport.getTrackingId());\n    46→\n    47→    HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt =\n    48→        new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n    49→            LocalDateTime.now(), completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, type, unLocode);\n    50→\n    51→    applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n    52→  }\n    53→}\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KVSuvnVZ36J4NuwGNUF7jY","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"78427443-5248-44f3-9011-b4bdbc555da3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VEeKo9vMztBZ7zyXYSoQPu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.rest;\n     2→\n     3→import javax.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     4→import javax.validation.constraints.Size;\n     5→import javax.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;\n     6→\n     7→/** Transfer object for handling reports. */\n     8→@XmlRootElement\n     9→public class HandlingReport {\n    10→\n    11→  @NotBlank(message = \"Missing completion time.\")\n    12→  @Size(\n    13→      min = 15,\n    14→      max = 19,\n    15→      message = \"Completion time value must be between fifteen and nineteen characters long.\")\n    16→  // TODO [DDD] Apply regular expression validation.\n    17→  private String completionTime;\n    18→\n    19→  @NotBlank(message = \"Missing tracking ID.\")\n    20→  @Size(min = 4, message = \"Tracking ID must be at least four characters.\")\n    21→  private String trackingId;\n    22→\n    23→  @NotBlank(message = \"Missing event type.\")\n    24→  @Size(\n    25→      min = 4,\n    26→      max = 7,\n    27→      message = \"Event type value must be one of: RECEIVE, LOAD, UNLOAD, CUSTOMS, CLAIM\")\n    28→  // TODO [DDD] Apply regular expression validation.\n    29→  private String eventType;\n    30→\n    31→  @NotBlank(message = \"UN location code missing.\")\n    32→  @Size(min = 5, max = 5, message = \"UN location code must be five characters long.\")\n    33→  private String unLocode;\n    34→\n    35→  @Size(\n    36→      min = 4,\n    37→      max = 5,\n    38→      message = \"Voyage number value must be between four and five characters long.\")\n    39→  private String voyageNumber;\n    40→\n    41→  public String getCompletionTime() {\n    42→    return completionTime;\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  public void setCompletionTime(String value) {\n    46→    this.completionTime = value;\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    50→    return trackingId;\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    54→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public String getEventType() {\n    58→    return eventType;\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  public void setEventType(String value) {\n    62→    this.eventType = value;\n    63→  }\n    64→\n    65→  public String getUnLocode() {\n    66→    return unLocode;\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  public void setUnLocode(String value) {\n    70→    this.unLocode = value;\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  public String getVoyageNumber() {\n    74→    return voyageNumber;\n    75→  }\n    76→\n    77→  public void setVoyageNumber(String value) {\n    78→    this.voyageNumber = value;\n    79→  }\n    80→}\n    81→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KVSuvnVZ36J4NuwGNUF7jY","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"424edd16-afe0-421f-878d-1966f7b17d8f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QG7rStdtT7VmizXMHou54b","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collections;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import java.util.Random;\n     9→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n    10→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    11→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    12→import javax.validation.constraints.Pattern;\n    13→import javax.validation.constraints.Size;\n    14→import javax.ws.rs.GET;\n    15→import javax.ws.rs.Path;\n    16→import javax.ws.rs.Produces;\n    17→import javax.ws.rs.QueryParam;\n    18→import org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal.GraphDao;\n    19→\n    20→@Stateless\n    21→@Path(\"/graph-traversal\")\n    22→public class GraphTraversalService {\n    23→\n    24→  private static final long ONE_MIN_MS = 1000 * 60;\n    25→  private static final long ONE_DAY_MS = ONE_MIN_MS * 60 * 24;\n    26→  private static final String UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE =\n    27→      \"UN location code value must be five characters long, \"\n    28→          + \"the first two must be alphabetic and \"\n    29→          + \"the last three must be alphanumeric (excluding 0 and 1).\";\n    30→  private final Random random = new Random();\n    31→  @Inject private GraphDao dao;\n    32→\n    33→  @GET\n    34→  @Path(\"/shortest-path\")\n    35→  @Produces({\"application/json\", \"application/xml; qs=.75\"})\n    36→  public List<TransitPath> findShortestPath(\n    37→      @NotNull(message = \"Missing origin UN location code.\")\n    38→          @Pattern(\n    39→              regexp = \"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\",\n    40→              message = \"Origin \" + UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE)\n    41→          @QueryParam(\"origin\")\n    42→          String originUnLocode,\n    43→      @NotNull(message = \"Missing destination UN location code.\")\n    44→          @Pattern(\n    45→              regexp = \"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\",\n    46→              message = \"Destination \" + UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE)\n    47→          @QueryParam(\"destination\")\n    48→          String destinationUnLocode,\n    49→      // TODO [DDD] Apply regular expression validation.\n    50→      @Size(min = 8, max = 8, message = \"Deadline value must be eight characters long.\")\n    51→          @QueryParam(\"deadline\")\n    52→          String deadline) {\n    53→\n    54→    List<String> allVertices = dao.listLocations();\n    55→    allVertices.remove(originUnLocode);\n    56→    allVertices.remove(destinationUnLocode);\n    57→\n    58→    int candidateCount = getRandomNumberOfCandidates();\n    59→    List<TransitPath> candidates = new ArrayList<>(candidateCount);\n    60→\n    61→    for (int i = 0; i < candidateCount; i++) {\n    62→      allVertices = getRandomChunkOfLocations(allVertices);\n    63→      List<TransitEdge> transitEdges = new ArrayList<>(allVertices.size() - 1);\n    64→      String fromUnLocode = originUnLocode;\n    65→      LocalDateTime date = LocalDateTime.now();\n    66→\n    67→      for (int j = 0; j <= allVertices.size(); ++j) {\n    68→        LocalDateTime fromDate = nextDate(date);\n    69→        LocalDateTime toDate = nextDate(fromDate);\n    70→        String toUnLocode = (j >= allVertices.size() ? destinationUnLocode : allVertices.get(j));\n    71→        transitEdges.add(\n    72→            new TransitEdge(\n    73→                dao.getVoyageNumber(fromUnLocode, toUnLocode),\n    74→                fromUnLocode,\n    75→                toUnLocode,\n    76→                fromDate,\n    77→                toDate));\n    78→        fromUnLocode = toUnLocode;\n    79→        date = nextDate(toDate);\n    80→      }\n    81→      candidates.add(new TransitPath(transitEdges));\n    82→    }\n    83→    return candidates;\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  private LocalDateTime nextDate(LocalDateTime date) {\n    87→    return date.plus(ONE_DAY_MS + (random.nextInt(1000) - 500) * ONE_MIN_MS, ChronoUnit.MILLIS);\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  private int getRandomNumberOfCandidates() {\n    91→    return 3 + random.nextInt(3);\n    92→  }\n    93→\n    94→  private List<String> getRandomChunkOfLocations(List<String> allLocations) {\n    95→    Collections.shuffle(allLocations);\n    96→    int total = allLocations.size();\n    97→    int chunk = total > 4 ? 1 + random.nextInt(5) : total;\n    98→    return allLocations.subList(0, chunk);\n    99→  }\n   100→}\n   101→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KVSuvnVZ36J4NuwGNUF7jY","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"8101221e-4d81-4948-9223-a7f458b20da7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013X1nwxTXdpbyyDJqt9GXDX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import javax.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;\n     7→\n     8→@XmlRootElement\n     9→public class TransitPath implements Serializable {\n    10→\n    11→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    12→\n    13→  private List<TransitEdge> transitEdges;\n    14→\n    15→  public TransitPath() {\n    16→    this.transitEdges = new ArrayList<>();\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  public TransitPath(List<TransitEdge> transitEdges) {\n    20→    this.transitEdges = transitEdges;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  public List<TransitEdge> getTransitEdges() {\n    24→    return transitEdges;\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  public void setTransitEdges(List<TransitEdge> transitEdges) {\n    28→    this.transitEdges = transitEdges;\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  @Override\n    32→  public String toString() {\n    33→    return \"TransitPath{\" + \"transitEdges=\" + transitEdges + '}';\n    34→  }\n    35→}\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KVSuvnVZ36J4NuwGNUF7jY","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"e1d2bd95-ca99-4b65-86ec-3c856d58dc3c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UugXdF39Va1ZMcnMZqCPQd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.Arrays;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Random;\n     8→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→public class GraphDao implements Serializable {\n    12→\n    13→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    14→\n    15→  private final Random random = new Random();\n    16→\n    17→  public List<String> listLocations() {\n    18→    return new ArrayList<>(\n    19→        Arrays.asList(\n    20→            \"CNHKG\", \"AUMEL\", \"SESTO\", \"FIHEL\", \"USCHI\", \"JNTKO\", \"DEHAM\", \"CNSHA\", \"NLRTM\",\n    21→            \"SEGOT\", \"CNHGH\", \"USNYC\", \"USDAL\"));\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  public String getVoyageNumber(String from, String to) {\n    25→    int i = random.nextInt(5);\n    26→\n    27→    switch (i) {\n    28→      case 0:\n    29→        return \"0100S\";\n    30→      case 1:\n    31→        return \"0200T\";\n    32→      case 2:\n    33→        return \"0300A\";\n    34→      case 3:\n    35→        return \"0301S\";\n    36→      default:\n    37→        return \"0400S\";\n    38→    }\n    39→  }\n    40→}\n    41→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KVSuvnVZ36J4NuwGNUF7jY","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"d66fb989-33cd-4961-a1df-f1bc0114b8dd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YBEtRpPhQjBWT7fJA28LVM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import javax.annotation.PreDestroy;\n     6→import javax.ejb.Singleton;\n     7→import javax.enterprise.event.ObservesAsync;\n     8→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     9→import javax.ws.rs.GET;\n    10→import javax.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import javax.ws.rs.Produces;\n    12→import javax.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    13→import javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→import javax.ws.rs.sse.OutboundSseEvent;\n    15→import javax.ws.rs.sse.Sse;\n    16→import javax.ws.rs.sse.SseBroadcaster;\n    17→import javax.ws.rs.sse.SseEventSink;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\n    21→\n    22→/** Sever-sent events service for tracking all cargo in real time. */\n    23→@Singleton\n    24→@Path(\"/cargo\")\n    25→public class RealtimeCargoTrackingService {\n    26→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    29→\n    30→  private Sse sse;\n    31→  private SseBroadcaster broadcaster;\n    32→\n    33→  private synchronized void ensureBroadcaster(Sse sse) {\n    34→    if (this.sse == null) {\n    35→      this.sse = sse;\n    36→    }\n    37→    if (broadcaster == null) {\n    38→      broadcaster = this.sse.newBroadcaster();\n    39→      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE broadcaster created.\");\n    40→    }\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  @GET\n    44→  @Produces(MediaType.SERVER_SENT_EVENTS)\n    45→  public void tracking(@Context SseEventSink eventSink, @Context Sse sse) {\n    46→    ensureBroadcaster(sse);\n    47→\n    48→    cargoRepository.findAll().stream().map(this::cargoToSseEvent).forEach(eventSink::send);\n    49→\n    50→    broadcaster.register(eventSink);\n    51→    logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE event sink registered.\");\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @PreDestroy\n    55→  public void close() {\n    56→    if (broadcaster != null) {\n    57→      broadcaster.close();\n    58→      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE broadcaster closed.\");\n    59→    }\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public void onCargoUpdated(@ObservesAsync @CargoUpdated Cargo cargo) {\n    63→    if (broadcaster != null) {\n    64→      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE event broadcast for cargo: {0}\", cargo);\n    65→      broadcaster.broadcast(cargoToSseEvent(cargo));\n    66→    }\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  private OutboundSseEvent cargoToSseEvent(Cargo cargo) {\n    70→    return sse.newEventBuilder()\n    71→        .mediaType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_TYPE)\n    72→        .data(new RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter(cargo))\n    73→        .build();\n    74→  }\n    75→}\n    76→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KVSuvnVZ36J4NuwGNUF7jY","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"cdbfae60-9d40-41c2-bfc8-e5e5b8913217"}
