{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011anmyVTiCsYopzPKZSGWGH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n     6→\n     7→/**\n     8→ * This interface provides a way to let other parts of the system know about events that have\n     9→ * occurred.\n    10→ *\n    11→ * <p>It may be implemented synchronously or asynchronously, using for example JMS.\n    12→ */\n    13→public interface ApplicationEvents {\n    14→\n    15→  void cargoWasHandled(HandlingEvent event);\n    16→\n    17→  void cargoWasMisdirected(Cargo cargo);\n    18→\n    19→  void cargoHasArrived(Cargo cargo);\n    20→\n    21→  void receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt);\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Rna5DMppV76Df7QzZauCu5","session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"b72efaad-bc2e-48a5-9d68-b505bf4c0018"}
