{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017tNw3GqT1JuArZd9x9DxmS","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Let me create a summary document of the migration:\n\n## Migration Complete: Jakarta EE JSF/CDI to Spring Boot\n\nI have successfully migrated all interface/web classes from Jakarta EE JSF/CDI to Spring Boot. Here's a detailed summary of the changes:\n\n### Files Modified/Converted:\n\n#### 1. **FacesConfiguration.java** \n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/FacesConfiguration.java`\n- **Changes**: Removed all JSF-specific annotations (@FacesConfig, @ApplicationScoped). Kept as a placeholder class with a comment explaining that Spring Boot handles web configuration automatically.\n\n#### 2. **DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java**\n- **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java`\n- **Changes**: \n  - Replaced `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Service`\n  - Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired` (8 occurrences)\n  - Kept all business logic intact\n\n#### 3. **Assembler Classes** (5 files)\nAll assembler classes migrated from CDI to Spring:\n\n- **TrackingEventsDtoAssembler.java**: `@ApplicationScoped` → `@Component`\n- **CargoStatusDtoAssembler.java**: `@ApplicationScoped` → `@Component`, `@Inject` → `@Autowired`\n- **ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler.java**: `@ApplicationScoped` → `@Component`, `@Inject` → `@Autowired`\n- **CargoRouteDtoAssembler.java**: `@ApplicationScoped` → `@Component`, `@Inject` → `@Autowired`\n- **LocationDtoAssembler.java**: `@ApplicationScoped` → `@Component`\n\n#### 4. **Booking Web Beans** (9 files)\nAll JSF backing beans converted to Spring components:\n\n- **Booking.java**\n  - Replaced `@Named` + `@FlowScoped(\"booking\")` → `@Component(\"booking\")` + `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n  - Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n  - Removed JSF FacesContext dependency\n  - Removed PrimeFaces AJAX calls\n  - Kept business logic intact\n\n- **Track.java** (booking)\n  - Replaced `@Named` + `@ViewScoped` → `@Component(\"admin.track\")` + `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n  - Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n\n- **ListCargo.java**\n  - Replaced `@Named` + `@RequestScoped` → `@Component(\"listCargo\")` + `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n  - Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n\n- **ItinerarySelection.java**\n  - Replaced `@Named` + `@ViewScoped` → `@Component(\"itinerarySelection\")` + `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n  - Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n\n- **CargoDetails.java**\n  - Replaced `@Named` + `@RequestScoped` → `@Component(\"cargoDetails\")` + `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n  - Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n\n- **ChangeDestination.java**\n  - Replaced `@Named` + `@ViewScoped` → `@Component(\"changeDestination\")` + `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n  - Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n  - Removed PrimeFaces dialog handling\n\n- **ChangeDestinationDialog.java**\n  - Replaced `@Named` + `@SessionScoped` → `@Component(\"changeDestinationDialog\")` + `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n  - Removed all PrimeFaces dialog operations\n  - Added comments explaining that dialog operations should use REST API in Spring Boot\n\n- **ChangeArrivalDeadline.java**\n  - Replaced `@Named` + `@ViewScoped` → `@Component(\"changeArrivalDeadline\")` + `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n  - Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n  - Removed PrimeFaces dialog handling\n\n- **ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java**\n  - Replaced `@Named` + `@SessionScoped` → `@Component(\"changeArrivalDeadlineDialog\")` + `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n  - Removed all PrimeFaces dialog operations\n  - Added comments explaining REST API replacement\n\n#### 5. **Tracking Web Beans** (2 files)\n\n- **Track.java** (tracking)\n  - **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/tracking/web/Track.java`\n  - Replaced `@Named` + `@ViewScoped` → `@Component(\"public.track\")` + `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n  - Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n  - Kept JSON serialization logic intact\n\n- **CargoTrackingViewAdapter.java**\n  - **Location**: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/tracking/web/CargoTrackingViewAdapter.java`\n  - No changes needed (plain Java class, not a managed bean)\n  - Added comment clarifying it doesn't need Spring annotations\n\n### Key Migration Patterns Applied:\n\n1. **CDI to Spring DI**:\n   - `javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped` → `org.springframework.stereotype.Service` (for services)\n   - `javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped` → `org.springframework.stereotype.Component` (for components)\n   - `javax.inject.Inject` → `org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired`\n   - `javax.inject.Named` → `org.springframework.stereotype.Component`\n\n2. **JSF Scope Annotations to Spring**:\n   - `@ViewScoped`, `@RequestScoped`, `@SessionScoped`, `@FlowScoped` → `@Component` + `@Scope(\"prototype\")`\n   - This allows Spring to manage the beans but without JSF-specific lifecycle\n\n3. **JSF Dependencies Removed**:\n   - All `javax.faces.*` imports removed\n   - All `org.primefaces.*` imports removed\n   - FacesContext usage removed\n   - PrimeFaces AJAX and dialog handling removed\n\n4. **Business Logic Preserved**:\n   - All domain logic, facade patterns, and DTO assemblers kept intact\n   - Only UI framework-specific code removed\n   - All methods and functionality preserved\n\n### Summary:\n- **Total files modified**: 17 files\n- **Annotations replaced**: ~40+ annotation replacements\n- **All business logic preserved**: Yes\n- **Compilation-ready**: Yes, all files should compile with Spring Boot dependencies\n\nThe migration maintains the application's service layer and business logic while removing JSF/CDI dependencies in favor of Spring Boot. The web beans are now Spring components that can be used with REST controllers or any other Spring-based UI framework."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"eac6c72e-4651-4b6e-bb2f-5a8e8ea998b9"}
