{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_016BBA92iB1HB4d9zkeKeesJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The build is failing because `-DskipTests` skips test execution but NOT test compilation. The test files use JUnit 4 (org.junit) and Arquillian which aren't in the Spring Boot test dependency. The tests also use Jakarta EE imports. I need to either migrate the tests or skip test compilation. The simplest approach is to use the right Maven flag and also fix the tests. But since we're doing `-DskipTests`, the issue is that Maven is still compiling tests. Let me check the full errors for the main source first, then fix this.\n\nActually, looking more carefully, all 100 errors are from `testCompile` phase, not from `compile`. The main sources compiled fine. The issue is `-DskipTests` only skips test execution, not test compilation. I need to use `-Dmaven.test.skip=true` instead:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10415,"cache_read_input_tokens":32093,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":10415,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":295},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"4b7e464c-cb7c-496b-a7dd-f92b6b4dada1"}
