{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01FUMFfsiGaz6ZGu1GxvhdYs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Still the same issue - `data.sql` is still executing before the table exists, even with `defer-datasource-initialization=true`. The problem is the `data.sql` file is running before Hibernate DDL auto. Since the `SampleDataGenerator` (now `ApplicationRunner`) already handles all the data loading, I don't need the `data.sql` at all. The `ApplicationSettings` table will be created by Hibernate from the JPA entity. The data.sql just inserts an initial row. Let me check what the ApplicationSettings entity looks like and then just remove data.sql:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1418,"cache_read_input_tokens":128090,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1418,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":328},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"efcb0f46-6f16-40bb-8c6c-f5bc57466f8b"}
