{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AJnm3juAjALHKinKwpinir","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Id;\n     6→\n     7→/**\n     8→ * Application settings. Although this is stored in the database, it is not a true part of the\n     9→ * domain model but simply an application infrastructure artifact.\n    10→ */\n    11→@Entity\n    12→public class ApplicationSettings implements Serializable {\n    13→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    14→\n    15→  @Id private Long id;\n    16→\n    17→  private boolean sampleLoaded = false;\n    18→\n    19→  public boolean isSampleLoaded() {\n    20→    return sampleLoaded;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  public void setSampleLoaded(boolean sampleLoaded) {\n    24→    this.sampleLoaded = sampleLoaded;\n    25→  }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"ed9f8b0c-e812-4f37-b061-cfbdff983d9e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Fa8gunknBUJ7ZHPHSoRvtG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is that `data.sql` tries to insert into `applicationsettings` before Hibernate creates the table. Even with `defer-datasource-initialization=true`, there may be a timing issue. The simplest fix: change `data.sql` to `schema.sql` + `data.sql` approach, or just use `spring.sql.init.mode=never` and handle everything in the ApplicationRunner. Since the SampleDataGenerator already uses `entityManager.find(ApplicationSettings.class, 1L)` to check if data is loaded, I just need the initial row. Let me just disable the SQL init and insert the ApplicationSettings row in the SampleDataGenerator itself:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":484,"cache_read_input_tokens":130205,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":484,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":332},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18f7ec53-4184-4cad-96bc-6843d85e3d1e","uuid":"48f9c708-1426-4d35-a013-2bec353e20fb"}
